HEADWORD: Proustite
<hw>Proust"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the French
chemist, J. L. <ets>Proust</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
sulphide of arsenic and silver of a beautiful cochineal-red color,
occurring in rhombohedral crystals, and also massive; ruby
silver.</def>⟦br⟧
